1. Gaps and Islands is one of the most important SQL interview patterns.
It's used when you need to find:
Consecutive dates
Consecutive IDs
Continuous ranges
Winning streaks
Active users
Human traffic sequences
WITH cte AS (
    SELECT
        id,
        dt,
        dt - ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY id
            ORDER BY dt
        ) AS grp
    FROM table_name
)
SELECT
    id,
    MIN(dt),
    MAX(dt),
    COUNT(*)
FROM cte
GROUP BY id, grp;
